          MODULE=YAML
         VERSION=0.71
          SOURCE=$MODULE-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$MODULE-$VERSION
      SOURCE_URL=http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/A/AD/ADAMK/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha1:4d75e95921fedfd570cf8eae29b02452aeb1af16
        WEB_SITE=http://search.cpan.org/~ingy/$MODULE-$VERSION
         ENTERED=20050801
         UPDATED=20100222
      MAINTAINER=perldude@lunar-linux.org
           SHORT="YAML - YAML Ain't Markup Language (tm)"
cat << EOF
The YAML.pm module implements a YAML Loader and Dumper based on the YAML 1.0
specification. <http://www.yaml.org/spec/>

YAML is a generic data serialization language that is optimized for human
readability. It can be used to express the data structures of most modern
programming languages. (Including Perl!!!)

For information on the YAML syntax, please refer to the YAML specification.
EOF
